<p>am new to IOS, i am trying to change my UIView controller after a user logs in. I am using NSURLConnection delegate</p>  <pre><code>-(void) connectionDidFinishLoading:(NSURLConnection *)connection{ // request has been completed [alertController dismissViewControllerAnimated:YES completion:nil]; result = [[NSString alloc] initWithData:_responseData encoding:NSUTF8StringEncoding];  //check contents of string if ([result containsString:@"success"]){     // TODO: client does exist  - navigate to otp authentication     UIStoryboard *mainstoryboard = [UIStoryboard storyboardWithName:@"Main" bundle:nil];     UIViewController *vc = [mainstoryboard         [[NSOperationQueue mainQueue] addOperationWithBlock:^{         if (![self.presentedViewController isBeingDismissed]){             [self.presentedViewController dismissViewControllerAnimated:YES completion:^{                 [self presentViewController:vc animated:YES completion:nil];             }];         }     }]; } </code></pre>  <p>So when i perform that UIView call on a simple button tap, it works. The error i am getting is the following:</p>  <pre><code>Warning: Attempt to dismiss from view controller &lt;ViewController: 0x7fc4717b5fb0&gt; while a presentation or dismiss is in progress! </code></pre>